The `handleWeightInput` handler triggers `onLog`, which performs an asynchronous IndexedDB write operation (`putLogEntry`) on every single keystroke. This can cause significant UI lag and typing interference, especially on slower devices. Changing `onInput` to `onChange` ensures the database write only occurs when the input is blurred or submitted.

```suggestion
            <input
              type="number"
              class="w-20 rounded-xl bg-flux-soft px-3 py-1.5 text-center text-sm font-medium tabular-nums text-flux-text-primary placeholder:text-flux-text-tertiary"
              value={weight ?? ''}
              placeholder={placeholder}
              onChange={handleWeightInput}
              data-testid={`weight-${index}`}
            />
```

<details>
<summary>References</summary>

1. Use 'onChange' instead of 'onInput' for text fields when the handler performs expensive side effects or input trimming, ensuring updates only occur on blur to prevent performance issues and typing interference.
